race.description: Nutrien Ag Solutions 'Star Cheers' Mdn Plate
race.comment: JUDGE JENNI (6) has switched stables and brings two close-up efforts from country Victoria on a 28-day return. Was heavily bet in both. That's good form for this. The inside gate will advantage and the leading jockey is booked suggesting she's pleasing the yard. Stablemate HENLEY EXTREME (5) came off a long break and led here as a $2 favourite first-up, beaten 1L over this distance. She's still well short of her NSW best and will be hard to roll with the extra fitness. SEDITIOUS AWARD (8) went close first-up in the same race. Keeps the 2kg claim but she gives away starts and always needs luck. WARRIORA (9) is lightly raced and has a jockey switch to Pires. Her Hobart effort three back would see her competitive and she may show more today.
